                     <interp inst="t18290611-311-person2227" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I met the prisoner going down Seymour-street: I asked what he had got - he said a bag of rice, which he got from Mr. Roberts', at the left-hand corner; I said he had better take it back, and he took it to where it came from.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A gentleman asked me to carry it to Chapel-street - I have only been in London six weeks.</p>
